.TH hsh 1 "April 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a basic UNIX shell that supports command execution with arguments,
environment variable usage (PATH), and built-in commands.

.SH USAGE
.TP
Start the shell:
.B ./hsh

.TP
Type a command and press Enter:
.B /bin/ls

.TP
Exit the shell:
.B exit

.TP
Print environment variables:
.B env

.SH AUTHORS
Maram Alsofyani and Hessah Alotaysh

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1)
